    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that sounds kinda like a stretch lol. so you're saying that letting the 1% keep more money is the way to \"naturally\" fix inequality? what about the counter-arguments from mainstream economists who say this just widens the gap and drains public resources? is there any actual consensus on whether this \"trickle down\" mechanism actually works in practice?",
